Title: Deduplicate _default_branch helper between beat.py and project-state.py
Created: 2026-05-05
Author: claude-agent

--- log ---
2026-05-05T18:30Z claude-agent created

--- body ---
## Context

`_default_branch(project)` — reads `refs/remotes/origin/HEAD`, strips the
`origin/` prefix, falls back to `"main"` — exists identically in two scripts:

- `scripts/beat.py` (extracted in PR #105 from inline code)
- `scripts/project-state.py` (added in PR #105)

Both scripts are standalone CLI tools with no shared import path today, so
the duplication was accepted as out-of-scope during the PR. The helper is
small but its fallback logic (`"main"`) is a policy decision that should
live in one place.

## Actions

1. Create `scripts/git_utils.py` (or `scripts/harness_utils.py`) with
   `_default_branch(project: Path) -> str` as the single definition.
2. Replace the duplicated implementations in `beat.py` and
   `project-state.py` with an import from the shared module.
3. Verify both scripts still run standalone (`python3 scripts/beat.py --help`,
   `python3 scripts/project-state.py .`).

## Test

Running `python3 scripts/project-state.py ~/.claude` returns a `git` block
with correct data on a repo whose default branch is not `main`.

## Exit criteria

- `_default_branch` defined in exactly one file under `scripts/`
- `beat.py` and `project-state.py` import it from there
- Both scripts pass a standalone smoke-test invocation
